# LogBid Landing Page Rules

## UI Components Styling Rules

### Input Components
- Always use explicit Tailwind classes instead of CSS variables
- Input styling: `border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-900 placeholder:text-gray-500`
- Focus states: `focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500`
- Never use: `border-input`, `bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`

### Select Components  
- Trigger: `border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-900`
- Content: `border-gray-200 bg-white text-gray-900`
- Items: `text-gray-900 focus:bg-blue-50 focus:text-blue-900`
- Never use: `bg-popover`, `text-popover-foreground`, `focus:bg-accent`

### Checkbox Components
- Default: `border-gray-300 bg-white`
- Checked: `data-[state=checked]:bg-blue-600 data-[state=checked]:text-white`
- Focus: `focus-visible:ring-blue-500`
- Never use: `border-primary`, `bg-primary`, `ring-ring`

### General Rules
- Always use concrete Tailwind color classes (gray-300, blue-500, etc.)
- Avoid CSS custom properties in component libraries
- Maintain consistent blue accent color (#1e3a8a) across components
- Use white backgrounds for form elements
- Ensure high contrast for accessibility
